XV. Of the same nature is that promise of the Romans, that Car- thage should be free: which, although, from the nature of the act, it could not be understood of full sovereign power, (for they had already lost the right of making war and other rights) yet it left some liberty to them, and at least so much, that they should not be eom- pelled to remove the seat of their goverument by extraneous com- mand.
